title: heracles_(housamo)
body:
[[Tokyo Afterschool Summoners]] character.
Designed by [[nikism|Sousuke]]

Transient from the world of Olympus. He is a hero born from a divine connection to lightning and a political scheme from System Olympus that magnifies belief. He is an extraordinarily strong warrior and has wandered many battlefields due to an oracle granted to him, but he also has a past of destroying everything dear to him due to a madness instilled into him. To atone for that crime, a new oracle was handed down that made him a slave for the span of three years and forced him into a role of absolute obedience to his master's orders. Brandished as a show of his superior's power with no thought of freedom and a healthy work environment, Heracles was exhausted in mind and body and sought the days without battle within his mind. Perhaps due to that, it seems like his current state as a slave feels more restful to him than his time as a bloodsoaked warrior. He's sympathetic to those who are given absurd abuse by their superiors and environment like him.

h4. External links

* "Housamo Wiki: Heracles":[https://housamo.wiki/Heracles]

title: frigate_bird
body:
Frigatebirds are a family of seabirds called Fregatidae which are found across all tropical and subtropical oceans.

They have predominantly black plumage, long, deeply forked tails and long hooked bills. Females have white underbellies and males have a distinctive red gular pouch, which they inflate during the breeding season to attract females.

title: african_elephant
body:
The African elephant ([i]Loxodonta[/i]) is a genus comprising two living elephant species, the African bush elephant ([i]L. africana[/i]) and the smaller African forest elephant ([i]L. cyclotis[/i]). Both are social herbivores with grey skin, but differ in the size and color of their [[tusks]] and in the shape and size of their ears and skulls.

African [[elephant]]s are distributed in Sub-Saharan [[Africa]], where they inhabit Sahelian scrubland and arid regions, tropical rainforests, mopane and miombo woodlands.

They are larger and have larger ears than [[Indian elephant|Indian elephants]].

title: cuttlefish
body:
Cuttlefish or cuttles are marine molluscs of the order Sepiida. They belong to the class [[Cephalopod|]]a, which also includes [[squid]], [[octopus|]]es, and [[nautilus (animal)|]]es.

Cuttlefish have large, W-shaped pupils, eight arms, and two [[tentacles]] furnished with denticulated suckers, with which they secure their prey.

title: trilobite
body:
Trilobites are a group of extinct marine arthropods. The first appearance of trilobites occurred in the Early Cambrian period (521 million years ago), and they disappeared in the end-Permian mass extinction about 252 million years ago.

Trilobites are characterized by a cephalon (head), thorax (body) and pygidium (posterior), and form a calcitic exoskeleton that is easily preserved as a [[fossil]].

title: samantha_(admiral_bahroo)
body:
Samantha is a female mascot character for the streamer Admiral Bahroo.  Depending on her design she may have [[brown hair|brown]] to [[orange hair]] or [[black hair|black]] & [[white hair|white]] [[two-tone hair]] with [[blue eyes]]. As of her second design she has sported clothing with a [[panda]] theme.

She is commonly depicted with Bahroo's other mascot, the small panda [[Umeru (admiral bahroo)|]].

Admiral Bahroo commissioned [[DyaRikku]] to create a "VTuber avatar":[https://twitter.com/dyarikku/status/1382609920512647169] featuring Samantha (3rd design) as a support avatar holding up the main avatar of Umeru. Due to technical issues with his commissioned computer his Live2D model was put offline.  After receiving a new commissioned computer from a new company he began streaming with Umeru alone until the beginning of March 2022 when he introduced his new VTuber avatar featuring Samantha's new updated 4th design.

h6. Standard designs

* 2nd Design (example: post #3712625): A panda hoodie with thighhighs
* 3rd Design (example: post #4290124): Blue sports crop top and pants under an off shoulder panda themed sweatshirt

title: shiso-chan_(tawawa)
body:
The first character to be depicted in the [i][[Getsuyoubi no Tawawa]][/i] series. On the series' seventh anniversary, she was featured for the first time since her debut and christened as the "Originator" (始祖 [i]shiso[/i]).

Also nicknamed the "Founding 〇〇〇an" (始祖の巨〇), a pun on the name of the Founding Titan from [i][[Shingeki no Kyojin]][/i] (始祖の巨人), as the omission of the last word's second kanji leaves it open for reinterpretation as [i]kyonyuu[/i] (巨乳, "huge breasts"), referring to [i][[Getsuyoubi no Tawawa]][/i]'s basic premise of revolving around female characters with breasts that are [[large breasts|large]] at their smallest. Incidentally, the pun also works in English, as the "tit" in "titan" is slang for a woman's breast.

title: yasu_(umineko)
body:
[b]Major spoilers below.[/b]

Character from [[Umineko No Naku Koro Ni]].

[spoiler]Yasu, whose real name is Sayo Yasuda, was the child born from the incestuous relationship between [[Ushiromiya Kinzou]] and his daughter [[Ushiromiya Beatrice]]. Kinzo offered him to [[Ushiromiya Natsuhi]] to raise as her own child, but refused his offer and shoved the servant carrying Yasu off of a cliff, gravely injuring him. Even though Yasu survived, his sexual organs were damaged beyond surgical repair, and was raised as a female within the Fukuin House on Rokkenjima.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]He adopts many other personas that appear throughout the series, originating as imaginary friends to cope with the loneliness of being raised in the Fukuin House. [[Shannon (umineko)|]], [[Kanon (umineko)|]], and [[Beatrice (umineko)|]] are the result of this, and each personality went on to live as separate figures who fell in love with [[ushiromiya_george|George]], [[ushiromiya_jessica|Jessica]], and [[ushiromiya_battler|Battler]], respectively. Most furniture that appear in Umineko were created this way as well; [[Virgilia (umineko)|]] and [[Ronove (umineko)|]] were respectively based on [[Kumasawa Chiyo|]] and [[Ronoue Genji|]], his parental figures, and the Seven [[Stakes of Purgatory]] were based on the Fukuin household servants he worked with that picked on him mercilessly.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]Due to being the last surviving child of Kinzo, he turns out to be the true heir of the Ushiromiya and inheritor of the gold promised for solving the epitaph. He is also behind the forgeries that are based off of the murders on Rokkenjima, and therefore Umineko's framing device. He later kills himself in [i]Requiem of the Golden Witch[/i] after surviving the murders and escaping with Battler.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]In an "ideal" existence in EP7, he is accepted by Natsuhi and later grows up to be [[Ushiromiya Lion]]. In EP5, he is known as "The Man from 19 Years Ago", a form of Sayo whose resentment towards his family took over all aspects of life. As this persona, Battler passed on harassing phonecalls to Natsuhi, attempting to implicate her as the killer on Rokkenjima, from a script which Sayo wrote.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]The name "Yasu" is derived the infamous "Yasu was the culprit" meme from [[Portopia Renzoku Satsujin Jiken]] ([i]The Portopia Serial Murder Case[/i]); in which it's revealed that the killer is Yasuhiro Mano, the player character's assistant who speaks and acts for him.[/spoiler]

The Magnificent Princess of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].
 
[[Princess]] from a neighboring country, possessing both prettiness and thorns. Firori's relationship with the [[demon|devil]] is fraught with secrets.

She has [[blonde hair]] and usually wears a [[tiara]]. Her eyes are [[blue eyes|blue]].

title: dia_(akuaya)
body:
The Devil Prince of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].
 
A boy who has become [[demon|devil]], spending eternity in nothingness. Once beloved as the [[prince]] of this land, he now exists by consuming the souls of men.

He has [[multicolored hair|white and black hair]] and typically wears a [[crown]]. Due to his [[heterochromia]], his left eye is [[red eyes|red]] and his right is [[blue eyes|blue]].

title: experimental_model_1_submachine_gun
body: The Experimental Model 1 Submachine gun is an 8mm submachine gun designed by Kijiro Nambu. Its most unusual feature is that its pistol grip doubles as the magazine well but due to the magazine's curvature, the grip is angled towards the muzzle in an awkward way. Design work was carried on with the The Experimental Model 2 Submachine gun, which used a more conventional layout.

title: working!!
body:
[b]WORKING!![/b] is a [[4koma]] by [[Takatsu Karino]], serialized in [b]Young Gangan[/b] since 2005. Originated from a [[working!! (web manga)|web manga]] started in 2002 also by Takatsu Karino.

The series has a TV anime adaptation which has run 3 seasons. The first season aired Spring 2010 and shared the same name as the manga. A second season aired Fall 2011 and was titled [i]Working'!![/i], with an apostrophe in the name.  The third and final season airing July, Summer 2015 and is titled [i]Working!!![/i], with three exclamation marks in the name. The alternative "export" name of the series is [b]Wagnaria!![/b] which is the name of the restaurant chain of the restaurant where most of the series takes place. 

It is a work-life comedy series with a quirky cast mostly consisting out of teens and young adults. Multiple characters in the series have feelings toward each other. However, this anime is for the most part not romance driven, so your mileage might vary.

title: gn_flag
body:
[b]SVMS-01X Union Flag Custom II "GN Flag"[/b]
A further modification of [[Graham Aker]]'s custom [[Union Flag]] equipped with the GN Drive Tau that was supposed to be installed in the GN-X unit intended for his personal use before he rejected it, citing personal reasons. The GN Drive was then installed on the Flag's left shoulder, with a connector cable powering the GN Beam Saber that had been taken from the [[Gundam Throne Eins]]. While it was a remarkably powerful unit, it still added up no more than a hasty modification of a machine that was not intended for GN Drive operation, so it lacked adequate G-force damping and put such considerable strain on Graham's body that he suffered grave internal injuries just from the maneuvering needed to keep up with the [[Gundam Exia]].

title: over_flag
body:
[b]SVMS-01O Over Flag[/b]
A further modification of the [[Union Flag]] intended for use by [[Graham Aker]]'s elite squadron, the "Overflags". Developed with piloting data from Graham's custom Flag, it boasts extreme performance at the cost of ease of handling - as it was intended to be used exclusively by ace pilots handpicked by Graham himself - and included innovations from the Custom Flag which made the unit greatly resemble a right-handed variant of Graham's personal, left-handed machine.

title: union_flag
body:
[b]SVMS-01 Union Flag[/b]
The Union's next generation general purpose MS, replacing the outdated Union Realdo. It built upon the Realdo's foundation, armed with the standard linear rifle and sonic blade, as well as carrying the defense rod for increased survivability. While it could also transform to and from a flight mode on the fly, this capacity was initially not used as a combat tool until demonstrated by [[Graham Aker]]'s extraordinary piloting skills, which led to this act of transforming in the midst of combat being dubbed the Graham Maneuver.

title: scissor_lift
body:
A scissor lift is a mechanical lifting platform used to provide temporary access for people and equipment to elevated and inaccessible areas. The device achieves vertical movement through the use of linked folding supports arranged in a crisscross or scissors-like pattern. Scissor lifts are designed to lift limited weights (usually less than a ton) and are capable of being set up and operated by one person. They are sometimes used while performing surface preparation, coating, or inspection activities.
